# Code Owners and Approval Requirements
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/managing-repository-settings/about-code-owners

# Global owners - require approval from core team for all changes
* @owner @core-team

# Critical security and governance files - require owner approval
docs/SECURITY.md @owner
docs/GOVERNANCE.md @owner
CODEOWNERS @owner
.github/workflows/deploy.yml @owner @core-team
.github/workflows/security.yml @owner @core-team

# Package and dependency management
package.json @core-team
pnpm-lock.yaml @core-team
requirements*.txt @core-team
Cargo.toml @core-team
Anchor.toml @core-team

# Documentation - core team approval for docs changes
docs/ @core-team
README.md @core-team

# Source code - standard approval process
src/ @core-team
website/ @core-team
scripts/ @core-team

# Configuration files
config/tsconfig.json @core-team
config/.eslintrc.json @core-team
config/vercel.json @core-team
.gitignore @core-team

# Build and deployment
.github/ @core-team
dist/ @core-team

# Tests - can be approved by any contributor
tests/ @*
*.test.* @*

# Content and data - broader approval
content/ @*
data/ @*
example-content.json @*